import json
from graphviz import Graph

# JSON data provided by user

            {"id": "USDA", "label": "United States Department of Agriculture"},

            {"source": "USDA", "target": "OS", "relationship": "operates"},
            {"source": "USDA", "target": "OCE", "relationship": "operates"}
        ]
    }
}

# Create a directed graph
dot = Graph(comment='USDA Organization Structure')

# Set the direction to left-to-right (LR) for horizontal layout
dot.attr(rankdir='LR')

# Add nodes with their labels
for node in json_data['directed_graph']['nodes']:
    dot.node(node['id'], node['label'])

# Add edges with relationship labels
for edge in json_data['directed_graph']['edges']:
    dot.edge(edge['source'], edge['target'], label=edge['relationship'])

# Render the graph to PNG
dot.render('usda_organization', format='png', cleanup=True)

print("Graphviz visualization created successfully!")
